      "comment_id" : 102258922,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "From the spring HtmlUtils comments:  * &lt;p&gt;For a comprehensive set of String escaping utilities,  * consider Apache Commons Lang and its StringEscapeUtils class.  * We are not using that class here to avoid a runtime dependency  * on Commons Lang just for HTML escaping. Furthermore, Spring&#39;s  * HTML escaping is more flexible and 100% HTML 4.0 compliant.  If you are already using Apache commons in your project probably you should use the StringEscapeUtils from apache"
