      "comment_id" : 79041342,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Nice. It doesn&#39;t use the &quot;html versions&quot; of the encodings (example: &quot;&#225;&quot; would be &quot;&amp;aacute;&quot; instead of &quot;&amp;#225;&quot;), but since the numeric ones work even in IE7 I guess I don&#39;t have to worry. Thanks."
