  "title" : "What is the recommended way to escape HTML symbols in plain Java?",
  "body" : "<p>Is there a recommended way to escape <code>&lt;</code>, <code>&gt;</code>, <code>\"</code> and <code>&amp;</code> characters when outputting HTML in plain Java code?  (Other than manually doing the following, that is).</p>\n\n<pre><code>String source = \"The less than sign (&lt;) and ampersand (&amp;) must be escaped before using them in HTML\";\nString escaped = source.replace(\"&lt;\", \"&amp;lt;\").replace(\"&amp;\", \"&amp;amp;\"); // ...\n</code></pre>\n"
